    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-03-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-03-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1287.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-03-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 6, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 9th ultimo, No. 870, and of
                    its accompaniments, relative to the opinions entertained by Lords Derby and
                    Russell of American affairs, as expressed in their speeches upon the Queen’s
                    address to Parliament, and the efforts of the insurgent emissaries in England,
                    to encourage a distrust as to the future policy of this government has been
                    received. Its suggestions have received attention in other despatches which go
                    out by this mail.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq.,<hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
